parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to the seat belt not latching or unlatching properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not lock
the seat belt buckle will not latch
the seat belt buckle is difficult to put on
the seat belt buckle sticks
the plastic piece on the seat belt buckle is coming off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor is not retracting right
the shoulder strap does not fully retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Anchor or Mount Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor or mount can cause the seat belt to not restrain the occupant properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The plastic that holds the shoulder belt to the lap belt fell off
the door-mounted seatbelt would not restrain the passenger when the door comes open
the shoulder belt separated from the lap belt where a rivet had broken loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt lock-up can cause the seat belt to not lock properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt lock-up causes failure
which may result in possible injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt System Failure in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt system in a crash can cause the occupant to not be properly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt restraint did not lock in a crash
the driver was thrown into the steering wheel although the shoulder and lap belt were in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Repeated alternator failures can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to stalling, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Alternator failure
repeated replacements
no significant drain on the vehicle's electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the dashboard
smoke filling the vehicle
trickle of fire under the dashboard
drops of fire falling into the vehicle
entire car engulfed in flames.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and running issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially strand the driver.
symptoms: Engine stalling
engine running after turning off the vehicle
engine check light coming on
vehicle cutting off while driving
hesitation when applying gas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition module failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Ignition switch failure
vehicle won't start
vehicle hesitates
ignition module failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may accelerate out of control, making it difficult for the driver to maintain control or stop the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
even when the foot is on the brake pedal
the throttle sticks in the open position
the vehicle lurches forward
the vehicle accelerates out of control
resulting in accidents or near-miss incidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A rough idle and vibration can cause discomfort, distraction, and decreased vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a rough idle
the vehicle vibrates excessively
the vehicle shakes or wobbles while driving.
